  "text": "To combat this, the body has evolved a method for various different stimuli-including exercise-to better access its DNA when required; that of histone modifications. Here, the histone proteins are acted on to allow the DNA to uncoil, making it more accessible for translation to the required protein. This primarily occurs via the addition of an acetyl group to the histone protein, which is catalysed by the histone acetyltransferase (HAT) enzyme group [CITATION_1] . In turn, the acetyl group is removed by histone deacetylase (HDAC) [CITATION_2] .",
